@StuartDNeilson I am lead to believe that the spike protein is what caused the damage!
Spike protein no longer in the Omicron variant, what is causing the damage?
So do all flu/cold cause this damage regardless?

@StuartDNeilson Feel really sorry that older people's freedoms/gains were not guaranteed in settings the vulnerable have to share with us like shops &amp; public transport.

Seems like a small price (temporary) to pay for a win-win.

The anti-everythings had no solution, did nothing to help us win.

@StuartDNeilson Before omicron, we could have controlled infection &amp; brought R below 1.

With omicron &amp; boosted roughly 50% reduction in verified infection, it is possible but will isn't there.

I think the least we can do now is to transparently protect old/vulnerable until infections crash.

@StuartDNeilson When it comes to vaccine equity, I think it's great to donate to the "get a vaccine, give a vaccine campaign."

It mightn't be a complete answer, but I think it's up to us &amp; government to at least pay our way for others.

https://t.co/1PbEdfo1m3

@StuartDNeilson I think it's an absolute waste, that we literally wasted 500k vaccines that could have been given to 70+, on NIAC approval, too late to donate.

We also boosted low risk at the same time as high risk. Many high risk are still not boosted.

No problem with high risk being D4'd. https://t.co/XCeLpeTJ1s
